-- Iran, Turkey Sign Deal for $1.3 Billion Natural Gas Pipeline, AFP Reports
-- Mike Harrison
-- 2010-07-24T09:26:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-24/iran-turkey-sign-deal-for-1-3-billion-natural-gas-pipeline-afp-reports.html

          
          
             Iran has signed a $1.3 billion deal
with Turkey to build a pipeline for gas exports of 60 million
cubic metres (2.1 billion cubic feet) a day, Agence France-
Presse said, citing local press reports.  
 Iran’s Deputy Oil Minister Javad Ouji, who is also the
director of the state-owned National Iranian Gas Company, signed
the deal with Turkey’s privately owned ASB group, the news
agency said.  
          
          


  


        